Someone is currently repairing my kitchen floor. And I'm doing it like I still have a job and I'm working from home, while I'm watching Too Hot to Handle.
If I could only manage to open the file. (Damn One Drive.)
*Voice of a hacker* I'm in.
And that's when he starts drilling super loudly. Hurrah.
It feels somewhat passive-aggressive to turn my air purifier up to maximum, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would even be completely okay if he weren't a mask opponent. And do I really need to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't until he's gone.
At least I've finally finished revising chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damned terrifying. Oh yes, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing a search and replace for … ➡️ Ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I'll stick with it. Natural language is usually fragmented, especially when you're emotional.
The handyman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he's almost done.
He went out to cut something (sounds like that, anyway). I sneaked a peek to see how far he is. There's still a lot to do :(
Still 7 pages in chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter, and it's looking pretty good – mainly changes to font and very small corrections to direct speech, and I need to make everything a bit more concise. But I could really use a break and a tea right now, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he's started vacuuming again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me that he had made an estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were too stingy and only paid for the part next to the door that's no longer in order. Feels much better now.
The house is being ventilated and my air purifier is running in the kitchen, while I'm drinking a tea in the garden!
